This paper explores the emotional dimensions of Valence, Arousal and Dominance (VAD) in software engineering, specifically in identifying symptoms of burnout and productivity loss. The paper analyzes textual communication in Jira issue reports, which falls under the software engineering sub-category (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential for text mining in work health assessment surveys, which could fall under human-computer interaction (cs.HC) or computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of a lexicon of English words with known VAD scores could also relate to natural language processing (cs.CL) or cybernetics (cs.CY). Finally, the analysis of issue report activities could relate to computer engineering (cs.CE) in terms of software development and project management.
